Ed,<br><br>
You make some very good points. I know what you mean, but don't know if it is possible for us to always be fair and considerate. How capable are we of listening and not talking and lecturing past each other? I'm as guilty as the next guy.<br><br>
The old adage used to be that one shouldn't discuss religion or politics. Now it appears that one shouldn't discuss the war in Vietnam.  If one does, he is doing so at his own risk.<br><br>
The solution is: this thread should remain for those who wish to enter and act goofy, while the other threads are still out there for us to vent or discuss. Start a thread for your above stated purpose and let's see.<br><br>
The challenge for all of us is to recognize in others the afflictions you have mentioned. It's not easy putting the other guys needs and wants ahead of ours. Ain't easy, but am willing to listen to what you have to say in a new thread.
